Class 4

CSS Selectors( Cascading Styling Sheet)
    It is another way of locating elements uniquely
    Syntax:
        tagname[Attribute='Attribute value']

        example: input[id='user-message']

        CSS does not give you an opportunity to identify an element by text

        Shortcuts for CSS:
            *Shortcut for className:"."-- classname //if space in class value it wont work
                tagname.classNameValue
                input.form-control
            *Shortcut for ID: "#"--ID
            tagname#IDValue //if space in id value it wont work
            input#ctl00_MainContent_username

            *contains() method in css:
            * symbol represents contains() method= tagname[attribute *= 'partial attribute value']
            input[id *= 'user']

            *starts-with method in css:
            ^ symbol represents starts-with method -- tagname[attribute ^= 'partial attribute value']
            input[type ^= 'sub']

            *ends-with method in css:
            $ symbol represents ends-with method -- tagname[attribute $= 'partial attribute value']
            input[id $= 'word']

WebElement Commands:
    consist of several methods where we can perform actions and get element state on the web page

    isEnabled() -- boolean value
    isSelected() -- boolean value
    isDisplayed() -- boolean value
    clear() -- void
    getText() -- String value
    getAttribute()-- String Value
